WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Good evening, and welcome to News At Six. I'm Sam Jenkins.

00:00:03.500 --> 00:00:08.800
Our top story tonight: Local authorities are urging residents to conserve water as reservoir levels drop to a 10-year low.

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:15.200
The prolonged dry spell has impacted agricultural production, and the government is considering emergency measures.

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:19.400
Moving on, we have an update on the ongoing budget negotiations in parliament.

00:00:19.400 --> 00:00:24.700
Sources indicate a breakthrough might be imminent, with key parties reportedly close to an agreement on education funding.

00:00:24.700 --> 00:00:28.000
And now, for something completely different.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:33.500
Breaking news: Scientists have confirmed that a newly discovered species of talking squirrel can predict lottery numbers.

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:38.900
The squirrels, found exclusively in a secret forest, are said to communicate telepathically with their chosen human companions.

00:00:38.900 --> 00:00:43.700
One lucky individual has already won multiple jackpots thanks to their furry friend.

00:00:43.700 --> 00:00:47.000
We're told the government is considering a nationwide squirrel adoption program.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:51.500
In other news, the city council announced plans today for a new public park.

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:56.200
It will feature walking trails, a children's play area, and an outdoor amphitheater for community events.

00:00:56.200 --> 00:01:00.000
That's all for News At Six. Join us tomorrow for more updates. Good night.